The objectives of this single center, randomized, double-blinded, placebo-controlled Phase I clinical study are to evaluate the safety and tolerability of five (5) single and four (4) multiple increasing oral doses of GIC-1001 compared to placebo, and to evaluate the pharmacokinetics of GIC-1001 following single and multiple-dose administration in 80 healthy, 18-50 years old male and female subjects.

 Moreover, the effect of food on the pharmacokinetics of GIC-1001 in healthy subjects will be assessed.

 This study is designed with an integrated, adaptive approach which allows the evaluation of single and multiples doses of GIC-1001 in a progressive, overlapped fashion.

